Package com.warzone.team08.VM.constants.interfaces

Interface SingleCommand

All Known Implementing Classes:
ApplicationExitService, DistributeCountriesService, EditMapService, LoadMapService, SaveMapService, ShowMapService, ShowMapService, ValidateMapService
public interface SingleCommand
Java interface which need to be implemented when command does not have any argument keys.

This type of command have zero or more values.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    java.lang.String execute​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> p_commandValues)
    This method will be called from CLI.

  • Method Details

    • execute

      java.lang.String execute​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> p_commandValues) throws VMException
      This method will be called from CLI. Accepts the list of arguments (can be empty). The method serves the purpose of the command without an argument key which may have value.
      Parameters:
      p_commandValues - Represents the values passed while running the command.
      Returns:
      Value of the string to be shown to the user.
      Throws:
      VMException - Throws the base class if there is invalid input or IOException
